          "body": "The narrator's verdict in verse 3 is precise: 'the sons of Israel gave the Levites from their inheritance these cities with their pasture lands, according to the command of the LORD.' The phrase 'from their inheritance' carries weight — every Levitical city came from someone else's allotment. Judah gave cities from Judah's territory; Ephraim gave cities from Ephraim's territory. The Levitical provision cost the host tribes something. This pattern will recur in Israel's later tithing legislation and in the New Testament's teaching on financial support for gospel ministry (1 Corinthians 9:13-14; Galatians 6:6). What the nation gave was a form of first-fruits — returning to God's ministers what God had first given to them. Verse 8 repeats the obedience formula, bracketing the entire list: 'as the LORD had commanded through Moses.' The repetition is deliberate; it is the narrator's insistence that obedience was complete, not selective."
